Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal (vapour + liquid) equilibrium data were measured for the {1,1,1-trifluoroethane (HFC-143a) + isobutene} as an alternative  refrigerant in the temperature range from (273.15 to 348.15) K at 15 K intervals. A circulating-type apparatus with on-line gas chromatography  was used in these experiments. The experimental data were correlated well by Peng Robinson equation of state using the  Wong Sandler mixing rules.
Citation.sTitle: (Vapour + liquid) equilibria of the {1,1,1-trifluoroethane (HFC-143a) + isobutene} system
